WEBVTT



00:00:08.768 --> 00:00:09.728
Welcome.

00:00:09.792 --> 00:00:13.728
As we walk with Jesus through the last weeks of his life,

00:00:13.824 --> 00:00:16.512
This week we're in the town of Capernaum.

00:00:16.800 --> 00:00:19.296
This was Jesus's hometown.

00:00:19.520 --> 00:00:22.464
And a place where he did a lot of his teaching.

00:00:22.208 --> 00:00:25.600
And performed many amazing miracles.

00:00:25.952 --> 00:00:30.272
He even raised Jairus's daughter from the dead there.

00:00:31.232 --> 00:00:34.912
What might we guess about the people of Capernaum?

00:00:35.008 --> 00:00:37.856
Knowing that they had a front row seat.

00:00:37.696 --> 00:00:40.800
To the amazing things Jesus was saying

00:00:40.576 --> 00:00:43.264
And the miraculous things he was doing.

00:00:43.904 --> 00:00:49.056
We might expect many of them to become enthusiastic followers of the Messiah.

00:00:49.632 --> 00:00:51.008
After all,,

00:00:50.784 --> 00:00:58.816
Don't we sometimes think, "Wow, I just wish Jesus could be right here in the room with me."

00:00:59.424 --> 00:01:04.672
That would take care of my dough. That would help me understand who he really is.

00:01:05.376 --> 00:01:08.224
Not so fast, says Matthew.

00:01:08.224 --> 00:01:10.944
In chapter 11, verse 12,

00:01:10.880 --> 00:01:13.792
He says, "and you, capernaum."

00:01:13.664 --> 00:01:16.416
Will you be lifted up to the heavens?

00:01:16.480 --> 00:01:19.680
No, you will go down to Hades.

00:01:19.840 --> 00:01:23.360
For the miracles that were performed in you

00:01:23.104 --> 00:01:25.760
Had been performed inside them.

00:01:25.632 --> 00:01:28.800
It would have remained to this day.

00:01:29.600 --> 00:01:33.952
Jesus takes this nice little Jewish town of Capernaum.

00:01:34.272 --> 00:01:36.256
And contrasts it

00:01:36.192 --> 00:01:38.976
with the evil city of Sodom.

00:01:38.912 --> 00:01:42.240
That God destroyed in his wrath.

00:01:42.048 --> 00:01:43.936
during the time of Abraham.

00:01:44.640 --> 00:01:47.680
And Jesus finds Capernaum lacking.

00:01:49.216 --> 00:01:50.720
We don't know.

00:01:50.528 --> 00:01:52.608
The Bible doesn't tell us

00:01:52.480 --> 00:01:58.112
What it was that caused the members of Capernaum, the people who lived there,

00:01:58.208 --> 00:02:00.224
To reject Jesus.

00:02:00.704 --> 00:02:03.936
Maybe they were bound by rules and tradition.

00:02:04.288 --> 00:02:08.000
Maybe they were distracted by their everyday lives.

00:02:08.448 --> 00:02:11.008
Maybe they heard Jesus teaching.

00:02:10.912 --> 00:02:13.568
That you had to become poor in spirit.

00:02:13.600 --> 00:02:16.992
Like a little child in humility and trust.

00:02:16.960 --> 00:02:18.208
And they said,

00:02:18.016 --> 00:02:19.936
Not for me.

00:02:20.768 --> 00:02:24.544
Maybe they just got used to having Jesus around.

00:02:24.704 --> 00:02:27.072
And they forgot the wonder.

00:02:27.008 --> 00:02:29.664
Of the kingdom of heaven that he taught.

00:02:29.568 --> 00:02:34.400
This amazing, new, beautiful countercultural.

00:02:34.336 --> 00:02:37.248
Thing he was bringing into existence.

00:02:38.528 --> 00:02:40.544
The lesson of Capernaum

00:02:40.448 --> 00:02:45.344
Is that complacency is a terrible entrapping sin.

00:02:45.664 --> 00:02:48.224
When we read God's Word,

00:02:48.480 --> 00:02:50.656
And don't take it to heart.

00:02:50.592 --> 00:02:52.448
When we worship

00:02:52.352 --> 00:02:54.944
With our minds somewhere else,

00:02:55.680 --> 00:03:00.896
When we don't look for the ways God is at work around us,

00:03:01.184 --> 00:03:03.456
And follow him in those words.

00:03:03.808 --> 00:03:05.920
We, too, run the risks.

00:03:05.696 --> 00:03:08.448
Are somehow missing the kingdom of heaven.

00:03:08.736 --> 00:03:10.816
Because we've missed its king.

00:03:11.840 --> 00:03:13.504
But Jesus

00:03:13.632 --> 00:03:16.128
He keeps going back to Capernaum.

00:03:16.608 --> 00:03:22.688
He keeps blessing them. He keeps teaching them. He keeps demonstrating for them.

00:03:22.432 --> 00:03:27.136
The loving heart of his father that wants none of them to perish.

00:03:28.032 --> 00:03:29.664
So this Lent

00:03:29.664 --> 00:03:32.480
Let's reject our own complacency.

00:03:32.640 --> 00:03:35.232
And receive from Jesus.

00:03:35.296 --> 00:03:38.080
The loving embrace he wants to offer.
